Full Description: ZebraPass leads the wireless ticketing and mobile commerce revolution by empowering movie theaters, entertainment venues, sports teams, and online ticketing portals worldwide with a system to better manage ticket and concession sales, as well as one-to-one marketing and consumer loyalty programs. The ZebraPass system premiered in June 2000 at the New Malibu Theater in Malibu, California. The ZebraPass business model is centered on enhancing revenue streams for entertainment venues and sports teams worldwide. Currently enabled by smart cards, the ZebraPass system has been created for a seamless transition to Bluetooth-enabled wireless devices such as cell phones, PDAs and other consumer appliances. The consumer logs onto the entertainment or sports venue's Web site using a PC or any Wireless Application Protocol (WAP) device to purchase their ticket, then proceeds directly to the event, avoiding long lines at the box office, ticketing kiosks and concession stands. To maintain consumer security, the ZebraPass system transfers the ticket information and consumer data using the highest level of SSL encryption.

Full Description: Adamant Valves is a professional sanitary valves manufacturer specialized in manufacturing a wide range of sanitary butterfly valves and sanitary ball valves. Adamant Valves uses advanced numerical control machine tools, processing and testing facilities to ensure that our products will meet your expectations for reliable performance and quality. We design and manufacture a wide range of stainless steel sanitary valves and fittings such as sanitary butterfly valves, sanitary ball valves, sanitary check valves, sanitary sight glasses, and sanitary unions, etc. They are widely used in the dairy, food, beverage, pharmaceutical, cosmetic, and other industrial markets. All our products are manufactured in accordance with different surface finishes, materials and industry standards including ISO, DIN, IDF, and SMS. They underwent extensive testing and field evaluation prior to introduction, incorporating advanced design characteristics with high quality materials. Adamant Valves also supplies a variety of sanitary pumps include Sanitary Centrifugal Pumps, Sanitary Rotary Lobe Pumps and Sanitary Liquid Ring Pumps. We offer a complete line of sanitary pumps to meet all of your dairy and food processing requirements. Adamant Valves has been audited and certified as meeting the full requirements of ISO 9001, CE, FDA, TUV,  including design, manufacture, inspection, customer service, and distribution functions. Our experienced engineers work closely with each customer to find out the best possible solutions. Our constant technical innovation combined with stringent quality control systems has enabled us to deliver high performance and outstanding value in sanitary applications. We are dedicated to improving the performance and value of our products, services, and solutions to meet your ever-changing requirements.

Description: Load testing for online applications
Full Description: CloudPuncher provides an online service for conducting Load and Performance tests of web sites and web-based applications using Cloud Computing infrastructure.  CloudPuncher can execute a load and performance test of any website or Rich Internet Application (RIA) by allocating an unlimited number of concurrent virtual user sessions in the cloud. Every cloud-based virtual user process executes a pre-recorded script representing various types of website or web application visitors. Test scripts can be easily configured to randomize content. CloudPuncher automatically allocates and procures the required hardware to execute load and performance tests. The service includes a monitoring component capable of instrumenting various elements of the server-side application including, but not limited to, operating system resources (both for Windows and Linux), web servers, databases, Java application servers and RIA remoting/messaging gateways.  As a result, testers can conduct real-time monitoring and reporting of the performance of their servers, including receiving information about any errors or bottlenecks resulting from traffic load.

Description: PremiseNET - a unique and patented home networking technology using  existing telephone wiring for multiple functions.
Full Description: The company, founded by Gordon Matthews, industry innovator and credited as one of the inventors of voice mail, has yet another unique concept to solve the frustrations of answering the telephone. The company's resulting primary product, called MAXX, employs PremiseNET - a unique and patented home networking technology using  existing telephone wiring for multiple functions.  Corporate focus also includes "next generation" design and development in advanced network technology, both in voice and data. Currently the company has thirty-one full time employees and over 40 independent sales and support staff. The results oriented  organizational structure enables efficient focusing of its core talent to provide innovative product design, hardware development, software design, market research, sales & marketing. The corporate headquarters are in Richardson, Texas, with its  software development offices in Austin, Texas. A  manufacturing agreement has been signed with Hitachi, thus guaranteeing the highest product quality.  The PremiseNET proprietary technology creates additional voice paths on standard telephone wire without disturbing the normal use of the telephone. This technology  allows multiple, simultaneous events such as talking to someone "on the outside", checking voicemail, plus room to room intercom. MAXX is the first product to use this breakthrough networking technology that uses existing telephone house wiring and  existing phones. Up to twelve telephones and/or faxes can be connected to the MAXX system.
